29/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Thursday (28 August), BiH Federation police announced a threatening letter has been received, addressed to BiH presidency member Sulejman Tihic.
According to the police, the letter was signed by the Chicago-based Gavrilo Princip organisation, reportedly part of the Serbian WWII Royalist rebel group.
Police have stepped up security for Tihic and are investigating the case.
(FENA, BBC - 28/08/03)
